Three phloroglucinol derivatives (24), (26) and (29) had monoisotopic mass 500.1685 Da and molecular formula C26H28O10 (
 Table 1). The presence diagnostic fragment ion m/z 249 allow identifying these compounds as dimers of isopentyl diformyl phloroglucinol, probably, sideroxylonals A, B and C (
 Table 1) (
 Eyles et al., 2003; 
 Sidana et al., 2012; 
 Okba et al., 2017; 
 Santos et al., 2019). However, due to the differences of parent ion fragmentation at the Orbitrap mass-spectrometer compared with the earlier used Bruker qTOF-MS (
 Okba et al., 2017; 
 Santos et al., 2019), the second diagnostic fragment for sideroxylonals with m/z 181 was not found (
 Table 1).
